name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: And so, surrounded by his friends and family, I address John Warner as he used to address me—“Well old friend, today you are at home.”

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: But today I celebrate John's impact over a three decade tenure in the Senate. The family he created from Senate colleagues—not just Senators, but committee staff, Capitol Police, food service workers, Senate gym employees. The ever-present curiosity and twinkle in the eye he had.

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: John Warner saw the Capitol under attack on January 6. He was deeply saddened by the assault on our democracy. We all should be. Today I am forced to wonder, will we step up to defend our nation as John did?

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: John joined the Navy as soon as he graduated from high school during World War II, and then rejoined the Marine Corps when the U.S. entered the Korean War. He did this at risk to his life, health, and career. But of course he prioritized defending the nation above all else.

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: As I entered public life, what impressed me most about John was his obvious belief that country and character count above all else. He was a Republican and I am a Democrat—but that never mattered. He never hesitated to prioritize his country over the orthodoxy of the day.

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: Long before I knew John Warner the patriotic public servant, I was honored to consider John a friend. It was only upon coming to the Senate—four years after he retired—that I came to fully understand the mark he left on the Senate, his beloved Commonwealth, and his country.

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: Today I was deeply honored to be able to share some of my thoughts at my dear friend John Warner's funeral—and I'd like to share some of them here as well, in memory of a man who truly exemplified love of country and character:

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: There must be a thorough review of all Tier 1 Group contracts and stronger State Department oversight of U.S. defense services provided to foreign nations—especially ones with problematic human rights records like Saudi Arabia, to ensure something like this never happens again.

name: Tim Kaine
tweet_text: These reports confirm what I feared to be true when I pressed Trump’s DOD nominee and Tier 1 board member Louis Bremer on this disturbing subject last year: Saudi nationals responsible for assassinating Mr. Khashoggi were trained by Tier 1 Group, a U.S. private security company. https://t.co/0lK69o3Ocv

name: Tim Kaine
